      <div class="post"><a name="1812449949971595768"></a>
        <h3> <a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~asuncion/personalblog/2007_04_01_archives.htm#1812449949971595768" title="permanent link"> Virginia Tech: There is Hope </a> </h3>
        
          <div class="post-body">
            <div class="small"><div style="clear:both;"></div>I cannot imagine the anguish and confusion that the Virginia Tech community is feeling right now.   Please take a moment to pray for the victims' families and friends.  This incident is a poignant reminder to all of us of the fragility of human life, and the depths of depravity that a human heart can achieve.  In days as dark and hellish as this one, it is vital for all of us to lay hold of the only eternal hope -- the <a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/%7Easuncion/peace.htm">hope of heaven</a>.<br /><br />There is a Book that we can turn to in times of trouble.  Here are some verses:<br /><br /><a href="http://www.blueletterbible.org/kjv/Jhn/Jhn011.html#25">Jhn 11:25</a> -- Jesus said unto her, <span class="SrptH">I am</span> the resurrection, and <span class="SrptH">the life</span>: <span class="SrptH">he that</span> believeth in me, though he were dead, yet shall he live:<br /><br /><a href="http://www.blueletterbible.org/kjv/Mat/Mat011.html#28">Mat 11:28</a> -- <span class="SrptH">Come</span> unto me, <span class="SrptH">all</span> [ye] that labour and are heavy laden, <span class="SrptH">and I</span> will give you rest.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.blueletterbible.org/kjv/Psa/Psa090.html#12">Psa 90:12</a> -- <span class="SrptH">So</span> teach [us] to number our days, <span class="SrptH">that</span> we may <span class="SrptH">apply [our] hearts</span> unto wisdom.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.blueletterbible.org/kjv/Mat/Mat005.html#4">Mat 5:4</a> -- Blessed [are] they that mourn: for they shall be comforted.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.blueletterbible.org/kjv/Psa/Psa046.html#1">Psa 46:1</a> -- God [is] our <span class="SrptH">refuge</span> and strength, <span class="SrptH">a very</span> present help in trouble.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.blueletterbible.org/kjv/Mat/Mat016.html#26">Mat 16:26</a> -- For <span class="SrptH">what is</span> a man profited, if he shall <span class="SrptH">gain</span> the whole world, and lose his own soul? <span class="SrptH">or</span> what shall a man give in exchange for his soul?<br /><br /><a href="http://www.blueletterbible.org/kjv/Rev/Rev021.html#4">Rev 21:4</a> -- And <span class="SrptH">God shall</span> wipe away all tears from their eyes; and there shall be <span class="SrptH">no</span> more death, <span class="SrptH">neither sorrow</span>, nor crying, neither shall there be any more pain: for <span class="SrptH">the former</span> things are passed away.<div style="clear:both; padding-bottom:0.25em"></div></div>
          </div>
          <p class="footer"><a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~asuncion/personalblog/2007_04_01_archives.htm#1812449949971595768" title="permanent link">11:30 PM</a> 
		    </p>
      </div>
